# Itinerate dev workflow

## Services and ports

| Service | Port | Start command |
|---------|------|---------------|
| Frontend (Vite) | 5173 | `cd frontend && npm run dev` |
| Backend (Spring Boot) | 8080 | `set -a && source backend/.env && set +a && cd backend && mvn spring-boot:run` |
| llm-proxy (Node) | 8081 | `cd llm-proxy && npm run start` |

Or proxy + backend together: `./scripts/dev.sh`

## When to restart

Spring Boot and llm-proxy do **not** hot-reload. Restart after changes:

- **Backend (8080):** any edit to `backend/src/**`, `backend/.env`, or `application.properties`
- **llm-proxy (8081):** any edit to `llm-proxy/server.js` or `llm-proxy/.env`
- **Frontend (5173):** Vite HMR handles normal `.tsx`/`.ts` edits — no restart needed

After changing `backend/.env`, always restart the backend with env loaded:

```bash
set -a && source backend/.env && set +a && mvn spring-boot:run
```

## API keys (all required for full functionality)

| Key | File | Used for |
|-----|------|----------|
| `CURSOR_API_KEY` | `llm-proxy/.env` | Itinerary planning + Maps MCP agent runs |
| `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` | `llm-proxy/.env` | Screenshot → place resolution via Google Maps MCP |
| `ITINERARY_LLM_API_KEY` | `backend/.env` | Any non-empty value (auth placeholder for local proxy) |
| `ITINERARY_VISION_API_KEY` | `backend/.env` | Screenshot inference via Google Gemini (Google AI Studio) |

Never commit `.env` files. After adding or changing keys, restart the affected service.

## Agent behavior

When modifying backend Java or `backend/.env`, restart the backend and verify port 8080 is listening before asking the user to test.

When modifying `llm-proxy/`, restart the proxy and verify port 8081 responds to `GET /health`.
